{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":861,"text":"We lost a lot of time at school\nlearning spelling."},{"time":5964,"text":"Kids are still losing a lot of time\nat school with spelling."},{"time":12585,"text":"That's why I want to share\na question with you:"},{"time":17720,"text":"Do we need new spelling rules?"},{"time":21572,"text":"I believe that yes, we do."},{"time":23890,"text":"Or even better, I think we need\nto simplify the ones we already have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29187,"text":"Neither the question nor the answer\nare new in the Spanish language."},{"time":33489,"text":"They have been bouncing around\nfrom century to century"},{"time":37727,"text":"since 1492, when in the first grammar\nguide of the Spanish language,"},{"time":43354,"text":"Antonio de Nebrija, set a clear and simple\nprinciple for our spelling:"},{"time":49120,"text":"\"... thus, we have to write words\nas we pronounce them,"},{"time":52063,"text":"and pronounce words as we write them.\""},{"time":54467,"text":"Each sound was to correspond\nto one letter,"},{"time":57793,"text":"each letter was to represent\na single sound,"},{"time":61142,"text":"and those which did not represent\nany sound should be removed."},{"time":67517,"text":"This approach, the phonetic approach,"},{"time":69996,"text":"which says we have to write\nwords as we pronounce them,"},{"time":73637,"text":"both is and isn't at the root of spelling\nas we practice it today."},{"time":78901,"text":"It is, because the Spanish language,\nin contrast to English, French or others,"},{"time":84426,"text":"always strongly resisted\nwriting words too differently"},{"time":89761,"text":"to how we pronounce them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91483,"text":"But the phonetic approach\nis also absent today,"},{"time":93776,"text":"because when, in the 18th century,\nwe decided how we would standardize"},{"time":97136,"text":"our writing,"},{"time":98372,"text":"there was another approach which guided\na good part of the decisions."},{"time":102409,"text":"It was the etymological approach,"},{"time":105275,"text":"the one that says we have to write words"},{"time":107492,"text":"according to how they were written\nin their original language,"},{"time":110670,"text":"in Latin, in Greek."},{"time":112236,"text":"That's how we ended up with silent H's,\nwhich we write but don't pronounce."},{"time":117060,"text":"That's how we have B's and V's that,\ncontrary to what many people believe,"},{"time":122372,"text":"were never differentiated\nin Spanish pronunciation."},{"time":126460,"text":"That's how we wound up with G's,"},{"time":128532,"text":"that are sometimes aspirated,\nas in \"gente,\""},{"time":131237,"text":"and other times unaspirated, as in \"gato.\""},{"time":133642,"text":"That's how we ended up\nwith C's, S's and Z's,"},{"time":137990,"text":"three letters that in some places\ncorrespond to one sound,"},{"time":141242,"text":"and in others, to two,\nbut nowhere to three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145800,"text":"I'm not here to tell you anything\nyou don't know from your own experience."},{"time":151368,"text":"We all went to school,"},{"time":154341,"text":"we all invested big amounts\nof learning time,"},{"time":159012,"text":"big amounts of pliant,\nchildlike brain time"},{"time":163734,"text":"in dictation,"},{"time":165365,"text":"in the memorization of spelling rules\nfilled, nevertheless, with exceptions."},{"time":170919,"text":"We were told in many ways,\nimplicitly and explicitly,"},{"time":174730,"text":"that in spelling, something fundamental\nto our upbringing was at stake."},{"time":181261,"text":"Yet, I have the feeling"},{"time":183586,"text":"that teachers didn't ask themselves\nwhy it was so important."},{"time":187245,"text":"In fact, they didn't ask themselves\na previous question:"},{"time":190397,"text":"What is the purpose of spelling?"},{"time":193993,"text":"What do we need spelling for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198619,"text":"And the truth is, when someone\nasks themselves this question,"},{"time":201560,"text":"the answer is much simpler\nand less momentous"},{"time":204673,"text":"than we'd usually believe."},{"time":206672,"text":"We use spelling to unify the way we write,\nso we can all write the same way,"},{"time":213415,"text":"making it easier for us to understand\nwhen we read to each other."},{"time":218407,"text":"But unlike in other aspects of language\nsuch as punctuation,"},{"time":224003,"text":"in spelling, there's no\nindividual expression involved."},{"time":230126,"text":"In punctuation, there is."},{"time":232117,"text":"With punctuation, I can choose\nto change the meaning of a phrase."},{"time":236097,"text":"With punctuation, I can impose\na particular rhythm to what I am writing,"},{"time":241546,"text":"but not with spelling."},{"time":243809,"text":"When it comes to spelling,\nit's either wrong or right,"},{"time":247410,"text":"according to whether it conforms\nor not to the current rules."},{"time":251694,"text":"But then, wouldn't it be more sensible\nto simplify the current rules"},{"time":257072,"text":"so it would be easier to teach, learn\nand use spelling correctly?"},{"time":263678,"text":"Wouldn't it be more sensible\nto simplify the current rules"},{"time":268209,"text":"so that all the time we devote today\nto teaching spelling,"},{"time":273585,"text":"we could devote to other language issues"},{"time":276677,"text":"whose complexities do, in fact,\ndeserve the time and effort?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282433,"text":"What I propose is not to abolish spelling,"},{"time":287421,"text":"and have everyone write however they want."},{"time":291878,"text":"Language is a tool of common usage,"},{"time":295822,"text":"and so I believe it's fundamental\nthat we use it following common criteria."},{"time":301609,"text":"But I also find it fundamental"},{"time":303805,"text":"that those common criteria\nbe as simple as possible,"},{"time":308175,"text":"especially because\nif we simplify our spelling,"},{"time":312033,"text":"we're not leveling it down;"},{"time":314870,"text":"when spelling is simplified,"},{"time":317567,"text":"the quality of the language\ndoesn't suffer at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322109,"text":"I work every day with Spanish\nGolden Age literature,"},{"time":326042,"text":"I read Garcilaso, Cervantes,\nGóngora, Quevedo,"},{"time":329670,"text":"who sometimes write \"hombre\" without H,"},{"time":332641,"text":"sometimes write \"escribir\" with V,"},{"time":335893,"text":"and it's absolutely clear to me"},{"time":338356,"text":"that the difference between those texts\nand ours is one of convention,"},{"time":343781,"text":"or rather, a lack of convention\nduring their time."},{"time":347398,"text":"But it's not a difference of quality."},{"time":350344,"text":"But let me go back to the masters,"},{"time":352792,"text":"because they're key characters\nin this story."},{"time":356170,"text":"Earlier, I mentioned this slightly\nthoughtless insistence"},{"time":361635,"text":"with which teachers pester and pester us"},{"time":364573,"text":"over spelling."},{"time":366097,"text":"But the truth is,\nthings being as they are,"},{"time":369593,"text":"this makes perfect sense."},{"time":371909,"text":"In our society, spelling serves\nas an index of privilege,"},{"time":377272,"text":"separating the cultured from the brute,\nthe educated from the ignorant,"},{"time":381684,"text":"independent of the content\nthat's being written."},{"time":386696,"text":"One can get or not get a job"},{"time":390031,"text":"because of an H that one put or did not."},{"time":392724,"text":"One can become\nan object of public ridicule"},{"time":395937,"text":"because of a misplaced B."},{"time":398612,"text":"Therefore, in this context,"},{"time":400812,"text":"of course, it makes sense to dedicate\nall this time to spelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405909,"text":"But we shouldn't forget"},{"time":408471,"text":"that throughout the history\nof our language,"},{"time":410695,"text":"it has always been teachers"},{"time":412659,"text":"or people involved\nin the early learning of language"},{"time":416608,"text":"who promoted spelling reforms,"},{"time":419152,"text":"who realized that in our spelling\nthere was often an obstacle"},{"time":423615,"text":"to the transmission of knowledge."},{"time":426028,"text":"In our case, for example,"},{"time":427719,"text":"Sarmiento, together with Andrés Bello,\nspearheaded the biggest spelling reform"},{"time":432296,"text":"to take place in the Spanish language:"},{"time":435725,"text":"the mid-19th century Chilean reform."},{"time":441894,"text":"Then, why not take over\nthe task of those teachers"},{"time":446379,"text":"and start making progress in our spelling?"},{"time":449796,"text":"Here, in this intimate group of 10,000,"},{"time":453072,"text":"I'd like to bring to the table"},{"time":454650,"text":"some changes that I find reasonable\nto start discussing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460207,"text":"Let's remove the silent H."},{"time":462599,"text":"In places where we write an H\nbut pronounce nothing,"},{"time":467711,"text":"let's not write anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469026,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470066,"text":"It's hard for me to imagine\nwhat sentimental attachment"},{"time":472728,"text":"can justify to someone\nall the hassle caused by the silent H."},{"time":477743,"text":"B and V, as we said before,"},{"time":480112,"text":"were never differentiated\nin the Spanish language --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":483006,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":484047,"text":"Let's choose one; it could be either.\nWe can discuss it, talk it over."},{"time":487376,"text":"Everyone will have their preferences\nand can make their arguments."},{"time":491030,"text":"Let's keep one, remove the other."},{"time":493898,"text":"G and J, let's separate their roles."},{"time":496929,"text":"G should keep the unaspirated sound,\nlike in \"gato,\" \"mago,\" and \"águila,\""},{"time":501375,"text":"and J should keep the aspirated sound,"},{"time":504695,"text":"as in \"jarabe,\" \"jirafa,\"\n\"gente,\" \"argentino.\""},{"time":510441,"text":"The case of C, S and Z is interesting,"},{"time":515793,"text":"because it shows that the phonetic\napproach must be a guide,"},{"time":519654,"text":"but it can't be an absolute principle."},{"time":522743,"text":"In some cases, the differences\nin pronunciation must be addressed."},{"time":527526,"text":"As I said before, C, S and Z,"},{"time":530456,"text":"in some places, correspond\nto one sound, in others to two."},{"time":533822,"text":"If we go from three letters\nto two, we're all better off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540247,"text":"To some, these changes\nmay seem a bit drastic."},{"time":545141,"text":"They're really not."},{"time":547346,"text":"The Royal Spanish Academy,\nall of language academies,"},{"time":550633,"text":"also believes that spelling\nshould be progressively modified;"},{"time":555562,"text":"that language is linked to history,\ntradition and custom,"},{"time":560472,"text":"but that at the same time,\nit is a practical everyday tool"},{"time":565119,"text":"and that sometimes this attachment\nto history, tradition and custom"},{"time":570037,"text":"becomes an obstacle for its current usage."},{"time":575619,"text":"Indeed, this explains the fact"},{"time":577752,"text":"that our language, much more than\nthe others we are geographically close to,"},{"time":584729,"text":"has been historically\nmodifying itself based on us,"},{"time":588281,"text":"for example, we went\nfrom \"ortographia\" to \"ortografía,\""},{"time":591959,"text":"from \"theatro\" to \"teatro,\"\nfrom \"quantidad\" to \"cantidad,\""},{"time":596084,"text":"from \"symbolo\" to \"símbolo.\""},{"time":598496,"text":"And some silent H's are slowly\nbeing stealthily removed:"},{"time":603927,"text":"in the Dictionary of the Royal Academy,"},{"time":606191,"text":"\"arpa\" and \"armonía\" can be written\nwith or without an H."},{"time":612007,"text":"And everybody is OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615452,"text":"I also believe"},{"time":618224,"text":"that this is a particularly appropriate\nmoment to have this discussion."},{"time":625397,"text":"It's always said that language\nchanges spontaneously,"},{"time":629432,"text":"from the bottom up,"},{"time":631322,"text":"that its users are the ones\nwho incorporate new words"},{"time":634619,"text":"and who introduce grammatical changes,"},{"time":638178,"text":"and that the authority --\nin some places an academy,"},{"time":642019,"text":"in others a dictionary,\nin others a ministry --"},{"time":645954,"text":"accepts and incorporates them\nlong after the fact."},{"time":650576,"text":"This is true only\nfor some levels of language."},{"time":654248,"text":"It is true on the lexical level,\nthe level of words."},{"time":657667,"text":"It is less true on the grammatical level,"},{"time":660945,"text":"and I would almost say\nit is not true for the spelling level,"},{"time":665155,"text":"that has historically changed\nfrom the top down."},{"time":669220,"text":"Institutions have always been the ones\nto establish the rules"},{"time":673279,"text":"and propose changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677143,"text":"Why do I say this is a particularly\nappropriate moment?"},{"time":681957,"text":"Until today,"},{"time":683349,"text":"writing always had a much more restricted\nand private use than speech."},{"time":690118,"text":"But in our time,\nthe age of social networks,"},{"time":694616,"text":"this is going through\na revolutionary change."},{"time":698311,"text":"Never before have people written so much;"},{"time":701379,"text":"never before have people written\nfor so many others to see."},{"time":706536,"text":"And in these social networks,\nfor the first time,"},{"time":709677,"text":"we're seeing innovative uses\nof spelling on a large scale,"},{"time":714741,"text":"where even more-than-educated people\nwith impeccable spelling,"},{"time":719374,"text":"when using social networks,"},{"time":721678,"text":"behave a lot like the majority of users\nof social networks behave."},{"time":727251,"text":"That is to say, they slack\non spell-checking"},{"time":730957,"text":"and prioritize speed and efficacy\nin communication."},{"time":736309,"text":"For now, on social networks,\nwe see chaotic, individual usages."},{"time":741764,"text":"But I think we have\nto pay attention to them,"},{"time":744805,"text":"because they're probably telling us"},{"time":747176,"text":"that an era that designates\na new place for writing"},{"time":751798,"text":"seeks new criteria for that writing."},{"time":756448,"text":"I think we'd be wrong\nto reject them, to discard them,"},{"time":761590,"text":"because we identify them as symptoms\nof the cultural decay of our times."},{"time":766586,"text":"No, I believe we have to observe them,\norganize them and channel them"},{"time":771548,"text":"within guidelines that better correspond\nto the needs of our times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778741,"text":"I can anticipate some objections."},{"time":783524,"text":"There will be those who'll say"},{"time":784978,"text":"that if we simplify spelling\nwe'll lose etymology."},{"time":790923,"text":"Strictly speaking, if we wanted\nto preserve etymology,"},{"time":794037,"text":"it would go beyond just spelling."},{"time":796491,"text":"We'd also have to learn\nLatin, Greek, Arabic."},{"time":801239,"text":"With simplified spelling,"},{"time":803894,"text":"we would normalize etymology\nin the same place we do now:"},{"time":809108,"text":"in etymological dictionaries."},{"time":812117,"text":"A second objection will come\nfrom those who say:"},{"time":815148,"text":"\"If we simplify spelling,\nwe'll stop distinguishing"},{"time":818890,"text":"between words that differ\nin just one letter.\""},{"time":822590,"text":"That is true, but it's not a problem."},{"time":826704,"text":"Our language has homonyms,\nwords with more than one meaning,"},{"time":831704,"text":"yet we don't confuse\nthe \"banco\" where we sit"},{"time":834490,"text":"with the \"banco\" where we deposit money,"},{"time":836586,"text":"or the \"traje\" that we wear\nwith the things we \"trajimos.\""},{"time":839859,"text":"In the vast majority of situations,\ncontext dispels any confusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847192,"text":"But there's a third objection."},{"time":852102,"text":"To me,"},{"time":855053,"text":"it's the most understandable,\neven the most moving."},{"time":858522,"text":"It's the people who'll say:\n\"I don't want to change."},{"time":862536,"text":"I was brought up like this,\nI got used to doing it this way,"},{"time":866269,"text":"when I read a written word\nin simplified spelling, my eyes hurt.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":872566,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":874391,"text":"This objection is, in part, in all of us."},{"time":880183,"text":"What do I think we should do?"},{"time":881696,"text":"The same thing that's always\ndone in these cases:"},{"time":884429,"text":"changes are made looking forward;\nchildren are taught the new rules,"},{"time":889866,"text":"those of us who don't want to adapt\ncan write the way we're used to writing,"},{"time":894423,"text":"and hopefully, time will cement\nthe new rules in place."},{"time":899264,"text":"The success of every spelling reform\nthat affects deeply rooted habits"},{"time":905795,"text":"lies in caution, agreement,\ngradualism and tolerance."},{"time":911663,"text":"At the same time, can't allow\nthe attachment to old customs"},{"time":916005,"text":"impede us from moving forward."},{"time":918775,"text":"The best tribute we can pay to the past"},{"time":922235,"text":"is to improve upon what it's given us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925255,"text":"So I believe that we must\nreach an agreement,"},{"time":927852,"text":"that academies must reach an agreement,"},{"time":930887,"text":"and purge from our spelling rules"},{"time":933849,"text":"all the habits we practice\njust for the sake of tradition,"},{"time":937578,"text":"even if they are useless now."},{"time":939685,"text":"I'm convinced that if we do that"},{"time":943185,"text":"in the humble but extremely\nimportant realm of language,"},{"time":947209,"text":"we'll be leaving a better future\nto the next generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953122,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}